-before-shootings.html}}</ref>\n|-\n| November 26, 1985\n| [[Spanaway, Washington]], United States\n| Heather Smith, 14\n| 3 dead\n|\n| At Spanaway Junior High School, a student, 14-year-old Heather Smith = who was apparently distraught over a failed romance and bad grades - fatally shot her her 15-year-old ex-boyfriend, Gordon Pickett, and another youth at the school, before killing herself. The second youth, 14-year-old Christopher Ricco, was shot while trying to prevent Smith from shooting Pickett.<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://apnews.com/075d33aa6600d2e6b30d969ba3edaf0d|title=''Distraught Over Losing Boyfriend, Girl Kills Two, Then Herself''|date=November 27, 1985}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 3, 1985\n| [[Concord, New Hampshire]], United States\n| Louis Cartier, 16\n| 1 dead\n| \n| At [[Concord High School (New Hampshire)|Concord High School]], Louis \"Louie\" Cartier, a 16-year-old male dropout, entered the school with a shotgun and took two students hostage. Responding officers fatally shot him as he aimed at a teacher.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p0qPt8jUr7E&t=9m|title=ABC News Nightline, Jan 29, 1986 \u2013 Challenger disaster one month after fatal school shooting|work=YouTube|accessdate=October 1, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Sarah Chalsma |url=http://www.concordmonitor.com/home/3438627-95/1985-concord-shooting-believe |title=My Turn: In 1985, Concord High was the site of another school shooting |publisher=concordmonitor.com |date=2012-12-19 |accessdate=January 14, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150627164824/http://www.concordmonitor.com/home/3438627-95/1985-concord-shooting-believe |archivedate=June 27, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Tom Mooney |url=http://www.apnewsarchive.com/1985/Wounded-Teen-Dies-Day-After-Police-Shots-Ended-Hostage-Incident/id-af067d94a4e319a31af445ae0190dcff |title=Wounded Teen Dies Day After Police Shots Ended Hostage Incident |agency=Associated Press |date=1985-12-04 |ac