6.ece|accessdate = 2009-04-18|language = Dutch}}</ref>\n|-\n| November 7, 2007\n| [[Tuusula]], Finland\n| Pekka-Eric Auvinen, 18\n| 9 dead\n| 1 injured\n| [[Jokela school shooting]]. 18-year-old student Pekka-Eric Auvinen opened fire with a [[.22 Long Rifle|.22-caliber]] [[semi-automatic handgun|semi-automatic]] [[SIG Mosquito|SIG Mosquito pistol]] at [[Jokela High School]], in [[Tuusula]], Finland. Six students, the school principal, and the school nurse were killed. The forty-minute attack ended when Auvinen shot himself in the head, later dying that evening at a [[Helsinki]] hospital.\n|-\n| December 11, 2007\n| [[Gurgaon]],<br>[[Haryana]],<br>India\n| Akash Vadav, 14;<br>Vikas Yadav, 13\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 14-year-old student Abhishek Tyagi was shot five times at the Euro International School, in [[Gurgaon]], India. Two other students, 14-year-old Akash Vadav and 13-year-old Vikas Yadav, were charged in connection with the shooting.<ref name=\"hindustani1212\">{{cite news|title=School students shoot classmate for \u2018bullying\u2019|date=2007-12-12|url =http://hindustantimes.com/StoryPage/StoryPage.aspx?id=df416321-98a6-4572-b0bf-c6c5fbf29902&MatchID1=4604&TeamID1=6&TeamID2=7&MatchType1=1&SeriesID1=1157&MatchID2=4575&TeamID3=8&TeamID4=2&MatchType2=1&SeriesID2=1147&PrimaryID=4604&Headline=School+students+shoot+classmate+for+%e2%80%98bullying%e2%80%99|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|accessdate = 2009-04-25}}</ref>\n|-\n| December 21, 2007\n| [[Union City, California|Union City]],<br>[[California]],<br>United States\n| Unknown\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Vernon Matthew Eddins, a 14-year-old student of [[James Logan High School]], was shot dead at the doorstep of Barnard-White Middle School, in [[Union City, California]].<ref name=\"usatodayviolencemap\">{{cite news|title=Mapping school violence|date=2009-04-12|agency= [[Associated Press]]|url =https://www.usatoday.com/news/nation/graphic-school-killings.htm|work=[[USA Today]]|accessdate = 2009-05-03}}</ref><ref name=\"baycitychronicle1221\">{{cite news|title=Boy shot dead in front of middle school |date=2007-12-21 |url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?file=/baycitynews/archive/2007/12/21/unioncity21.DTL&tsp=1 |work=[[San Francisco Chronicle]] |accessdate=2009-05-11 |url-status=dead |first=Bay |last=City |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071225145824/http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?file=%2Fbaycitynews%2Farchive%2F2007%2F12%2F21%2Funioncity21.DTL&tsp=1 |archivedate=December 25, 2007 }}</ref> Police issued that the shooting was prompted by an argument escalating between [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Latino]] and [[African American]] groups of teenagers. No suspects were ever sought.<ref name=\"yollinchronicle1223\">{{cite news|first=Patricia|last=Yollin|title=Boy shot near middle school IDd|date=2007-12-23|url =http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article/article?f=/c/a/2007/12/23/BADIU3PC9.DTL|work=[[San Francisco Chronicle]]|accessdate = 2009-05-11}}</ref><ref name=\"ktvu1222\">{{cite news|title=Victim Of Union City Shooting Was A Student|date=2007-12-22|publisher=[[KTVU]]|url =http://www.ktvu.com/news/14913119/detail.htmlws/archive/2007/12/21/unioncity21.DTL&tsp=1|archive-url =https://archive.today/20130127203242/http://www.ktvu.com/news/14913119/detail.htmlws/archive/2007/12/21/unioncity21.DTL&tsp=1|url-status =dead|archive-date =2013-01-27|accessdate = 2009-05-11}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 8, 2008\n| [[Lower Alsace Township, Pennsylvania]], United States\n| Ian Chimenko, 13\n|\n| 3 injured\n| 13-year-old student Ian Chimenko stabbed three of his classmates in a classroom at Antietam Middle-Senior High School, in [[Lower Alsace Township, Pennsylvania|Lower Alsace]], [[Pennsylvania]]. Chimenko held faculty members at bay with a blowtorch before being subdued.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://readingeagle.com/article.aspx?id=75504 |title=3 Antietam students stabbed in class; charges to be filed |publisher=Readingeagle.com |date=2008-01-09 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 29, 2008\n| [[Mannar District]], [[Sri Lanka]]\n| [[LTTE]]\n| 17 dead\n| 14 injured\n| [[Madhu school bus bombing]]. An accidental explosion of a [[claymore mine]] planted by the [[LTTE]] (Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam), a [[Sri Lanka]]n [[Insurgent|militant]] organization, targeting the armed forces, resulted in the deaths of 17 civilians, including 11 children on a school bus in the [[Mannar District]]. Sri Lanka was engaged in a war against LTTE, known for attacking and killing innocent civilians in many occasions throughout a period of more than 30 years of its operation.<ref name=children>{{cite news|author= Reddy, B. Muralidhar|url= http://www.spur.asn.au/Choronology_of_LTTE_Tamil_Tiger_Attacks_on_Passanger_Buses_and_Trains.htm|title= Chronology of LTTE Tamil Tiger Terrorist's recent attacks on passenger buses and trains|accessdate= 2008-05-09|url-status= dead|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080720103635/http://www.spur.asn.au/Choronology_of_LTTE_Tamil_Tiger_Attacks_on_Passanger_Buses_and_Trains.htm|archivedate= 2008-07-20}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 4, 2008\n| [[Memphis, Tennessee]], United States\n| \n|\n| 1 injured\n| At Hamilton High School, a 16-year-old student was shot in the leg during an argument with another student over rap music. The victim's injury was not life-threatening.<ref>{{cite web| title = Police investigate shooting inside classroom at Hamilton High|publisher= [[WMCTV]]| date = February 4, 2008| url = http://www.wmctv.com/story/7818497/police-investigate-shooting-inside-classroom-at-hamilton-high| first = Kontji| last = Anthony| accessdate = August 31, 2013| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140302022256/http://www.wmctv.com/story/7818497/police-investigate-shooting-inside-classroom-at-hamilton-high| archive-date = 2014-03-02| url-status = dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 12, 2008\n| [[Oxnard]],<br>[[California]],<br>United States\n| Brandon David McInerney, 14\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 15-year-old [[Lawrence Fobes King]] was shot in th